OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FJapan PM fires aide over   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fanti-LGBT remarks          
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Japan's Prime Minister Fumio Kishida   
OL,6, has fired a government aide who made   
OL,7, derogatory remarks about LGBT couples. 
OL,9,FMasayoshi Arai reportedly said he would
OL,10,Fnot want to live next to, or look at,  
OL,11,Fpeople in same-sex relationships.      
OL,13,FMr Arai also warned that permitting gay
OL,14,Fmarriage in Japan would lead to many   
OL,15,Fabandoning the country.                
OL,17,FMr Kishida said the remarks were       
OL,18,F"outrageous" and "completely           
OL,19,Fincompatible" with his government's    
OL,20,Fpolicies.                              
